content.value: If a man’s (hair on his) head falls out in tufts: [you bandage his head] with pulverized @i{saḫlû}-cress, [you should not remove (the bandage) for three days, (but) on the fourth day you shave his head], you wash his head with water from @i{uḫūlu}-alkali, (and) you anoint it repeatedly with oil, [(then) you crush cedar (and) cypress, you mix them in cedar oil, you anoint his head (with the mixture) for three days, (and then) he will recover].
